RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M All Weather Track CR: 79. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $2,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VANISKY tracked the early pace, raced four wide into the first turn, advanced along the backstretch run, roused three wide on the far turn, ran in pursuit of the pacesetter to mid-stretch, confronted QUE SERA SIR RALPH nearing the furlong marker, battled with that foe to the sixteenth-pole, assumed command and kept to task in the late stages to prevail. TAM'S TIME unhurried in the early stages, roused along the second turn, swung widest into the stretch run, rallied five wide in the drive, closed well in deep stretch, could not reel in the winner in the final stages and was up for place. QUE SERA SIR RALPH sent leaving the break, drifted in entering the first turn, dictated terms through moderate early fractions, set the pace to the quarter marker, drifted in under right-handed in mid-stretch, was confronted by VANISKY nearing the furlong marker, met that bid to the sixteenth-pole but could not keep pace late and was well clear for third. GOVERNOR ARTHUR forwardly placed in the early stages, checked repeatedly while rank and in tight along the first turn, recovered nearing the five-eighths pole, stalked the moderate pace to the second turn, lost ground nearing the quarter marker, swung four wide for the drive and did not offer a late rally. LOVE OF THE SPORT shuffled leaving the break and was away a step slowly, allowed to settle, saved ground into the far turn and was not a factor. RUNAWAY KRISTIN away in good order, close up to the pace while saving ground on the first turn, stalked the moderate pace to the second turn, asked for run at the top of the lane, steadied off of heels when QUE SERA SIR RALPH drifted in in mid-stretch, took up and dropped back in the final furlong. THERE WERE TWO STEWARDS INQUIRIES INTO THE RUNNING OF THIS RACE. THE FIRST CONCERNED THE RUNNING ON THE FIRST TURN INVOLVING GOVERNOR ARTHUR. THE STEWARDS RULED UNANIMOUSLY THAT WHILE GOVERNOR ARTHUR CAME IN TIGHT ALONG THE FIRST TURN AND CHECKED REPEATEDLY, THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH BASED ON THE INCIDENT. THE OTHER INQUIRY CONCERNED RUNAWAY KRISTIN STEADYING IN MID-STRETCH. IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT QUE SERA SIR RALPH DRIFTED IN NEARING THE EIGHTH POLE, CAUSING RUNAWAY KRISTIN TO TAKE UP, AND IN DOING SO COST THAT RUNNER THE OPPORTUNITY OF A BETTER PLACING. QUE SERA SIR RALPH WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM THIRD AND PLACED LAST. THERE WAS ALSO A TRAINER'S OBJECTION LODGED BY THE TRAINER OF GOVERNOR ARTHUR FOR THE INCIDENT ON THE FIRST TURN AND A JOCKEY'S OBJECTION LODGED BY THE RIDER OF RUNAWAY KRISTIN FOR THE INCIDENT IN MID-STRETCH.

ENTRY.OWNER: Addae Kwasi and James Bob A

BERNIE'S BIG BOY allowed the pace scenario to develop through the first quarter mile, took a four wide path through the turn and into the stretch, ran somewhat evenly through the stretch and was never a threat but was able get up for third. THAT'S BIND BABE stalked the pacesetter to the turn, made a bid for the lead at the top of the stretch, was unable to gain any ground late and was outfinished for third.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAN'THELPFALLIN (IRE) allowed to settle, maintained position through the backstretch run, swung widest into the drive, closed fast while five wide in upper stretch, quickly overtook DANCE LADY inside of the furlong marker and pulled away in the late stages as much the best. DANCE LADY tracked the solid early pace, made a three wide middle move heading to the far turn, vied for the lead three deep nearing the top of the lane, battled with DRESS REHEARSAL in the drive, could not hold off CAN'THELPFALLIN in mid-stretch, weakened in the late stages and was well clear for third. DRESS REHEARSAL asked to show early speed after a good beginning and dictated terms to the first turn, set a pressured pace into the backstretch run then ceded the lead to LAST INNING, tracked that foe to the far turn, vied for the lead from the rail nearing the quarter marker, battled with DANCE LADY to mid-stretch and faded in the final furlong. LAST INNING squeezed a bit at the start and away a step slowly, hard sent to contest the early pace, assumed command along the backstretch run and set solid fractions to the half-mile marker, vied between runners to the quarter marker, dropped back in upper stretch and tired in the drive.

HARBOR SKY lunged at the start then was shuffled in the first few strides and was off slowly, was allowed to settle along the first turn, made a middle move and was well placed into the far turn, raced three wide into the drive and weakened. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLUE WILDCAT content to track mid-pack down the backstretch, made a sweeping move around the turn to get into contention, was even with the leaders as the field turned for home, dueled with PRESSKIT the length of the stretch and was able to get a nose in front of that determined rival at the wire. PRESKITT broke in and bumped lightly with BLUE WILDCAT after the break then easily gained the early advantage but was content to cede the lead to ICONIC SKY, chased that one to the quarter pole, angled to the inside for the stretch run and ran on well only to lose a head bob at the wire. MISCHIEVOUS CURLIN unhurried down the backstretch, responded when asked to pick it up with three furlongs to run, swung four wide into the turn and closed willingly to gain third. SEEMS LOGICAL not asked for speed from the break, raced the first quarter mile under a hold, nearly clipped heels with TEN THE SMART WAY near the half mile marker then backed off, stayed to the inside and summoned a good late run up the rail in the stretch and was gaining on the leaders late but ran out of race track. OCTANE (BRZ) lagged near the rear of the field after the break, pulled on the rider passing the half mile pole, was still last through the turn, stayed inside for the stretch run and finish with a grinding late run to be part of the crowed photo finish. LADY'S SERMON lacked early speed despite being asked after the break, came under a hard ride from the seven-sixteenths pole, went four-wide through the turn and swung out into the five path for the stretch run, finished with some interest while still wide and was gaining at the finish. ICONIC SKY broke slowly then rushed up to seize the early lead, held an open lead to the quarter pole then wilted when challenged at the top of the stretch. TEN THE SMART WAY came away well from the outside, was content to track the pace from mid-pack while about four wide, moved forward through the turn in tandem with BLUE WILDCAT inside, then began to struggle passing the three-sixteenths pole and was no factor from that point.
